To accommodate the backup agent tool's specifications, the system admin team at xFusionCorp Industries requires the creation of a user with a non-interactive shell. Here's your task:
Create a user named ammar with a non-interactive shell on App Server 1.



List all users:
cat /etc/passwd

TO just usernames only:
cut -d: -f1 /etc/passwd

To specifically check if ammar already exists:
id ammar

The common non-interactive shell is:
/sbin/nologin

(or sometimes /usr/sbin/nologin depending on the server)

We can verify this using:
which nologin

To create an user
sudo useradd -s /usr/sbin/nologin ammar

Verify:
grep ammar /etc/passwd


